Titolo: Enduro (video game)

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Enduro is a racing video game designed by Larry Miller for the Atari 2600 and published by Activision in 1983. Miller previously wrote Spider Fighter for Activision. The object of the game is to complete an endurance race, passing a certain number of cars each day to continue the next day. The visuals change from day to night, and there is occasional inclement weather. A ZX Spectrum port was published in 1984
Activision released The Great American Cross-Country Road Race, which expands upon the design of Enduro, for home computers in 1985.

Genere: Racing 

Valutazione: N/A
